-- To run --
go inside project folder
cd ~/Documents/report_service
or

cd ~/Documents/GRP/cmn-service/services/reporting-service/python/report_service
source venv/bin/activate
pip3 freeze
./manage.py runserver

cd ~/Documents/GRP/astprc-report-service/python/report_service
source venv/bin/activate
pip3 freeze
./manage.py runserver

-- Details --

1. Install virtual-environment-
sudo pip3 install virtualenv


2. Create a virtual-environment
   -go inside the project folder
virtualenv -p python3 venv(name of the virtual-environment)


3. Activate virtual-environment
source venv(name of the virtual-environment)/bin/activate

to deactivate-
deactivate


4. To check what is installed in virtual-environment
pip3 freeze


5. To install dependencies in virtual-environment
pip install -r requirements.txt
(All the dependencies are declared in requirements.txt)


6. To run Django
./manage.py runserver

project will run on 127.0.0.1:8000 or localhost:8000



